Great spot with reaaaaly good coffee. Ava was awesome

My coffee was excellent, but my food was ice cold in the middle.  That being said, I will still come back. It’s a great place for my family living in Charlotte, Mooresville, and Statesville to meet.

My daughter and I stopped by for a couple of iced coffees on a VERY hot day. Somehow the people that ordered after us got served first and the server told them she gave them the rest of the ice. We were served "iced" coffee completely warm with not even one ice cube. My cold brew was also extremely bitter, and I couldn't even drink it.  We waited about 20 minutes for our order. There are too many other options around for coffee. I will not be returning.
My drink, the service and the atmosphere are great! Almost 18 dollars for an iced coffee and a pre-made microwaved sandwich, not so much.
The atmosphere and coffee here is great! Our barista Sidney went above and beyond explaining the menu! I would recommend!
I got the shake Sonora. It was delicious.  The girl at the register was very friendly.
My drink was very good and the atmosphere was so cozy! My barista’s name was Sidney and I got a strawberry matcha. I will definitely be going back!

Sid was super efficient and friendly!
Good strong coffee.
Dog friendly.
Huge space.
Amazing hidden gem in Mooresville right off Main St.
I'm so sorry to leave this comment. Waiting more than 18 minutes for a coffee, and to top it off with burnt milk, is unacceptable.

Very sad visit today . How is it fair to charge $1.35 for alternative milk then only get a splash of it ? Then when you ask for more you get an attitude and they give you a tiny shot like it would just fill a small dropper . Then on my other coffee I order a latte and I am handed the cup with everything just dumped in a cup . Nothing stirred or anything . Looks more like a macchiato. Then the cold brew I ordered ( the one with the very expensive droplet of oat milk ) was missing the flavor so I ask the girl to add a shot of the vanilla and she snapped at said “ it’s in there “ sorry high school girl it’s not . I currently work in the Coffee business now the last 14 years I know when a coffee is missing something . I came here to support the local shop in this area but will not be back. And on top of that how do you run out of 90 % of your breakfast items before 10:00AM ? Poor leadership here ….

Great atmosphere (LOVE the large map!) and friendly service, but the drinks are overly sweet (even after asking for half sweet) and pretty pricey. The vegan PB bar was delicious though! I’d love to see CR offer some cleaner house syrups instead of just Monin.
The food was great and the service it only took 5 minutes and I got all my stuff I ordered. And it was really cozy in there💗 overall it was great

First time stopping by, as I had time to spare and wanted to try a new coffee shop; I would normally swing through a local drive through (not a “Starbucks girly” here). There was only one barista running the entire store on a Sunday morning at 9am. I ordered 3 standard menu drinks (honey cinnamon latte, vanilla latte and an iced strawberry matcha) to-go for my friends and I after waiting in line for nearly 30 minutes. I was leaving shortly after 10am. My honey cinnamon latte was just okay.

There’s plenty of seating both inside and outside. Opportunity to have real plants vs the faux ivy, but that’s just personal preference.

The barista was exceptionally nice and apologetic for the wait. She handled the pressure politely and professionally. I genuinely felt so bad that she was the only one on staff for the morning.

Recommend that the owners either make the process more efficient (larger espresso machine, automatic coffee grounds dispenser, shut off online orders when the walk-in business is busy, etc.) and ensure that weekends have good coverage. The prices are competitive to other shops that staff up more.

We buy our at home coffee here, which is quite nice. We don't often get drinks. When we do it usually takes forever because there is only one person working. That's no fault of the person, but just be prepared. The service otherwise is always top notch and everyone who works there is super nice. I appreciate that they have remained dog friendly throughout their changes.

Went here because I had no power at my apartment. Cute little place got there right when they opened and had to wait just a little for the lady to open up but other than that pretty solid place. Easy location, nice staff.
Was at a private gathering, staff, coffee. Pastry was Great...

This establishment is one of my favorites in Mooresville!
I recently hosted an event there and everything went perfectly!
Besides that everything on the menu is great!

Coffee Republic in Morrisville is a hidden gem that’s quickly become one of my favorite spots. The first thing you notice when you walk in is the cool, modern interior—it’s got a relaxed, inviting vibe with thoughtful design touches that make it feel unique and comfortable.

The space is surprisingly spacious, with plenty of seating for individuals, small groups, or even casual work meetings. Whether you're grabbing a quick coffee or planning to camp out for a bit with your laptop, there's always a good spot to settle in.

The staff is incredibly friendly and welcoming. They greet you with a smile and are happy to answer questions or make recommendations. That kind of warm service makes a big difference.

And of course—the coffee is great. Smooth, rich, and well-crafted every time. Whether you're into lattes, cold brews, or just a classic cup of drip, they do it right.

If you’re in the Morrisville area and looking for a place to relax, catch up on work, or just enjoy a good cup of coffee, Coffee Republic is definitely worth checking out.
Cool spot near downtown Mooresville. Good spot to do some work and relax. Clean and friendly. Good music.
Always get the best coffee and customer service at this location

I generally have a good deal of empathy for service workers and don't think I've ever left a negative review before for anything. But I'm honestly just done. I've had some iffy customer service here before but today was the last straw. It was incredibly busy and the workers were clearly stressed out, so I don't blame them for having waited a half hour for my partner's and I's (completely unaltered, main menu drinks). What I do find unacceptable was the way we never received either an apology or an explanation when bringing the fact that they'd forgotten to make one of the drinks in our order and had moved on to other customers after us. The woman making the drinks at first started to argue, then got this "oh crap" look on her face and spoke quietly with the other worker. She then made my partners drink without any other explanation, and no apologies.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Jenny, I’d like to apologize on behalf of the employees - we had a no call no show today, and I do apologize if the baristas did not give the best service. Please send me an email, and I will compensate for your experience today. Info@coffeerepub.com

reviews_data.review_text: This is a great place to go for coffee!  Their lattes are amazing, the service is great, and it has a comfortable atmosphere.

Me and my boyfriend went here this morning and it was awful. First off ran out of plain bagels at 10a.m on a sunday?? and then spent 6 dollars on a large coffee that was like a dunkin small. he got a bacon egg and cheese sandwich and it was literally a frozen sandwich for 8 dollars. the employee was beyond rude and i would not recommend this to anyone.

Met my daughter here for brunch. I got the Aztec mocha coffee. I just asked for light cayenne, and it was perfect. We both got a breakfast burrito.  They were the perfect size, and the price was right to come back. Nice atmosphere.

The only complaint I would really have is that there was only one person working. So it was a little bit of a wait time you couldn't just like run in and out of here, but we had intended to sit and stay and eat in the establishment. It might be quicker if you're ordering multiple of the same drink, but we had different drinks. So it did take a little time to get those out. Because the woman was trying to like make drinks and food and take new orders as people came in.

Coffee Republic in Morrisville is a hidden gem that’s quickly become one of my favorite spots. The first thing you notice when you walk in is the cool, modern interior—it’s got a relaxed, inviting vibe with thoughtful design touches that make it feel unique and comfortable.

The space is surprisingly spacious, with plenty of seating for individuals, small groups, or even casual work meetings. Whether you're grabbing a quick coffee or planning to camp out for a bit with your laptop, there's always a good spot to settle in.

The staff is incredibly friendly and welcoming. They greet you with a smile and are happy to answer questions or make recommendations. That kind of warm service makes a big difference.

And of course—the coffee is great. Smooth, rich, and well-crafted every time. Whether you're into lattes, cold brews, or just a classic cup of drip, they do it right.

If you’re in the Morrisville area and looking for a place to relax, catch up on work, or just enjoy a good cup of coffee, Coffee Republic is definitely worth checking out.
